33namespace cricket {
34
35enum DtlsTransportState {
36 // Haven't started negotiating.
37 DTLS_TRANSPORT_NEW = static_cast<int>(webrtc::DtlsTransportState::kNew),
38 // Have started negotiating.
39 DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTING =
40 static_cast<int>(webrtc::DtlsTransportState::kConnecting),
41 // Negotiated, and has a secure connection.
42 DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED =
43 static_cast<int>(webrtc::DtlsTransportState::kConnected),
44 // Transport is closed.
45 DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED = static_cast<int>(webrtc::DtlsTransportState::kClosed),
46 // Failed due to some error in the handshake process.
47 DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED = static_cast<int>(webrtc::DtlsTransportState::kFailed),
48};
49
50webrtc::DtlsTransportState ConvertDtlsTransportState(
51 cricket::DtlsTransportState cricket_state);
52
53enum PacketFlags {
54 PF_NORMAL = 0x00, // A normal packet.
55 PF_SRTP_BYPASS = 0x01, // An encrypted SRTP packet; bypass any additional
56 // crypto provided by the transport (e.g. DTLS)
57};
58
59// DtlsTransportInternal is an internal interface that does DTLS, also
60// negotiating SRTP crypto suites so that it may be used for DTLS-SRTP.
61//
62// Once the public interface is supported,
63// (https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#rtcdtlstransport-interface)
64// the DtlsTransportInterface will be split from this class.
65class DtlsTransportInternal : public rtc::PacketTransportInternal {
66 public:
67 ~DtlsTransportInternal() override;
68
69 virtual DtlsTransportState dtls_state() const = 0;
70
71 virtual int component() const = 0;
72
73 virtual bool IsDtlsActive() const = 0;
74
75 virtual bool GetDtlsRole(rtc::SSLRole* role) const = 0;
76
77 virtual bool SetDtlsRole(rtc::SSLRole role) = 0;
78
79 // Finds out which TLS/DTLS version is running.
80 virtual bool GetSslVersionBytes(int* version) const = 0;
81 // Finds out which DTLS-SRTP cipher was negotiated.
82 // TODO(zhihuang): Remove this once all dependencies implement this.
83 virtual bool GetSrtpCryptoSuite(int* cipher) = 0;
84
85 // Finds out which DTLS cipher was negotiated.
86 // TODO(zhihuang): Remove this once all dependencies implement this.
87 virtual bool GetSslCipherSuite(int* cipher) = 0;
88
89 // Gets the local RTCCertificate used for DTLS.
90 virtual rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate> GetLocalCertificate()
91 const = 0;
92
93 virtual bool SetLocalCertificate(
94 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate) = 0;
95
96 // Gets a copy of the remote side's SSL certificate chain.
97 virtual std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLCertChain> GetRemoteSSLCertChain() const = 0;
98
99 // Allows key material to be extracted for external encryption.
100 virtual bool ExportKeyingMaterial(const std::string& label,
101 const uint8_t* context,
102 size_t context_len,
103 bool use_context,
104 uint8_t* result,
105 size_t result_len) = 0;
106
107 // Set DTLS remote fingerprint. Must be after local identity set.
108 virtual bool SetRemoteFingerprint(const std::string& digest_alg,
109 const uint8_t* digest,
110 size_t digest_len) = 0;
111
112 ABSL_DEPRECATED("Set the max version via construction.")
113 bool SetSslMaxProtocolVersion(rtc::SSLProtocolVersion version) {
114 return true;
115 }
116
117 // Expose the underneath IceTransport.
118 virtual IceTransportInternal* ice_transport() = 0;
119
120 // F: void(DtlsTransportInternal*, const DtlsTransportState)
121 template <typename F>
122 void SubscribeDtlsState(F&& callback) {
123 dtls_state_callback_list_.AddReceiver(std::forward<F>(callback));
124 }
125
126 template <typename F>
127 void SubscribeDtlsState(const void* id, F&& callback) {
128 dtls_state_callback_list_.AddReceiver(id, std::forward<F>(callback));
129 }
130 // Unsubscribe the subscription with given id.
131 void UnsubscribeDtlsState(const void* id) {
132 dtls_state_callback_list_.RemoveReceivers(id);
133 }
134
135 void SendDtlsState(DtlsTransportInternal* transport,
136 DtlsTransportState state) {
137 dtls_state_callback_list_.Send(transport, state);
138 }
139
140 // Emitted whenever the Dtls handshake failed on some transport channel.
141 // F: void(rtc::SSLHandshakeError)
142 template <typename F>
143 void SubscribeDtlsHandshakeError(F&& callback) {
144 dtls_handshake_error_callback_list_.AddReceiver(std::forward<F>(callback));
145 }
146
147 void SendDtlsHandshakeError(rtc::SSLHandshakeError error) {
148 dtls_handshake_error_callback_list_.Send(error);
149 }
150
151 protected:
152 DtlsTransportInternal();
153
154 private:
155 RTC_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(DtlsTransportInternal);
156 webrtc::CallbackList<const rtc::SSLHandshakeError>
157 dtls_handshake_error_callback_list_;
158 webrtc::CallbackList<DtlsTransportInternal*, const DtlsTransportState>
159 dtls_state_callback_list_;
160};
161
162} // namespace cricket

164#endif // P2P_BASE_DTLS_TRANSPORT_INTERNAL_H_
